title: dressing for potato salad
directions: Mix well and pour over potatoes.
Then mix again until potatoes are covered.

title: rhubarb upside down cake
directions: Mix together egg, sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla, salt and milk.
Mix together in bottom of cast-iron skillet the 2 Tbsp. melted butter and brown sugar.
Put about 2 cups rhubarb over mixture in skillet.
Pour batter over rhubarb.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, let sit a few minutes. Turn skillet upside down on cake plate.
Cake will come right out.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Cut bread slices into 4 squares.
Fit 1/3 of bread tightly in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, 1/3 of onion and 1/3 of cheese.
Press down, repeat instructions twice.
Beat eggs, add mustard, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over casserole contents, cover and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 2 hours before serving and drizzle with melted butter.
One hour before serving, bake in a preheated 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until firm in center.
(If you double this recipe, use only 5 cups milk.) Serves 8.

title: mama's best turkey
directions: You will need 1 large size Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: matt's teriyaki chicken
directions: Cook chicken to about 4/5 the way done.
Mix in bowl honey, lime juice, teriyaki sauce, garlic, and ginger.
Add sauce to chicken and green onion.
Serve over rice.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine in mixing bowl first 4 ingredients.
Beat well and stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add 1 cup water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Fill muffin cups 1/3 to 1/2 full with chocolate batter.
Top each with 1 heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna patties
directions: Beat egg well. Grate potato and onion and add to the beaten egg.
Add tuna, bread crumbs, salt and pepper; mix well.
Make into 5 patties.
Then saute in small amount of butter or oil until brown on both sides.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Salt zucchini; let sit for 30 minutes.
Rinse and drain. Butter a 4-quart dish.
Layer 1/2 zucchini, 1/2 tomatoes, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 bread.
Start again.
Bake until zucchini is tender, about 45 minutes, at 350°.

title: microwave chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Combine morsels in 1 3/4-quart or larger microwave casserole and microwave at 50% power (covered) 4 to 6 minutes.
Stir and add peanut butter halfway through cooking time.
Stir in peanuts and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper or into small paper cups. Refrigerate until set.

title: red sour cherry salad
directions: Strain juice from cherries and boil juice with sugar until sugar dissolves.
Pour over 2 packages of gelatin and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add 2 cups of water, orange juice and rind, lemon juice and rind, the cherries and pineapple.
Chill until partially thickened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan mold.
Chill until firm.

title: green fried tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4 inch thick and dip in egg mixture, then into bread crumbs.
Fry in butter and oil until brown on both sides.

title: cranberry cookie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium size saucepan, melt margarine over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Beat in sugars, egg and vanilla with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in flour and baking powder, salt and cinnamon until thoroughly combined. Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Grease bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Press batter evenly into pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pronto pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip together until it thickens.
Fold in drained crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate for 5 hours or until pie thickens.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and melt.
Add syrup and mix well.
Add over sliced sweet potatoes in layers.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until syrup thickens and forms glaze.

title: snicker bar dessert
directions: Soften ice cream in big bowl.
Add topping and beat.
Add peanut butter and mix in.
Add pudding and thoroughly blend.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan and freeze well.
Cut into squares and serve frozen.
Makes 8 servings; each serving equals 1/4 milk, 1/2 fruit, 1/2 protein, 1/2 fat and 40 optional calories.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers very thin. Sprinkle salt on top. Mix well. Invert plate on top of cucumbers. Put something real heavy on plate for about 2 hours. This will get the water and bitterness out. Rinse cucumbers well and drain. Peel and slice onion thinly. Add whipping cream and half of the half and half. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Toss sliced potatoes in 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1 cup water.
Drain.
Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Spoon undiluted soup over top.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours, or 4 hours on high.

title: celery delight
directions: Cook celery in salted water (boiling) for 8 minutes; drain. Combine celery, undiluted soup, pimentos and water chestnuts. Turn into 6-cup casserole.
Heat butter until hot; add almonds and stir until pale brown.
Scatter over casserole; scatter crumbs over top (can be mixed with almonds, if desired, first).
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken well with damp paper towels.
Combine flour, ginger, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Shake chicken in mixture, coating well.
Brown chicken in butter, turning often.
Combine pineapple, soy sauce and water; pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, combine cornstarch and water.
Add sugar, soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, ground ginger and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Brush the chicken (split in halves lengthwise) with soy mixture.
Place chicken halves, skin side down, in greased shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Brush with soy mixture every 10 minutes.
Turn chicken, skin side up.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Brush occasionally.
Drain pineapple and add during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: roman noodles
directions: Combine onion, green pepper and oil in a 2-quart casserole. Cook in microwave on Full power for 2 to 3 minutes, until onion and green pepper are tender.
Stir in mushrooms with liquid, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook in microwave, covered, on Full power for 3 minutes and heated through.
Stir in noodles and water.
Cook in microwave, covered, on Full power for 9 to 12 minutes, until noodles are tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Stir in the peas.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.
Serves about 4 to 5 people.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper, sugar, basil and oregano.
Butter baking dish and alternate layers of tomato mixture and bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a hot oven, 400°, for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix and cook together until thick, about 20 minutes.
Stir while cooking.

title: strawberries devonshire
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons whipping cream; beat until fluffy.
Whip remaining cream; fold into cream cheese mixture.
Serve with fresh strawberries.

title: sour cream pastries
directions: With pastry blender, cut butter or margarine into flour until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Combine egg yolk and sour cream; blend into flour mixture.
Chill dough several hours or overnight. Divide dough into 4 portions, keeping each part refrigerated until ready to use.
Roll each part to 10-inch circle on floured surface. Spread 2 tablespoons apricot preserves.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons coconut and 1 tablespoon nuts.
Cut each circle into wedges and roll into crescent.
Sprinkle with sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix and cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add sifted mixture alternately with sour milk, a bit at a time, to creamed mixture until all together.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of 2-quart dish.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread on top of beans.
Drain olives and green chilies.
Layer remaining ingredients on top of sour cream, ending with cheese on top.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold with tortilla chips.

title: baked spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water; bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup chips and vanilla.
Stir until chips melt and mix is smooth. Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Slowly add flour mixture.
Stir in the rest of the chips.
Spread into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 16 squares.

title: squash dish
directions: Mix soup, onion, carrot and sour cream. Add to mashed squash. Mix dressing with margarine.
Add half to squash mixture. Add other half to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Crumble cornbread into a large mixing bowl.
Add corn, tomatoes, onions and peas.
Mix until evenly moist.
Add ham and mix thoroughly.
Stuff mixture into bell peppers.
Place in large glass baking dish. Spoon excess stuffing around peppers and place 1 strip bacon on top of each pepper. Bake 40 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute medium onion in butter.
Add flour.
In another boiler, heat 4 cups chicken stock and milk.
When hot, add to flour.
Boil green onions, carrots and celery until tender; drain some.
Add Cheez Whiz and mustard.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Note:
Need 1 square foil about 10 x 10-inches.

title: mixed vegetable medley
directions: Heat vegetables and water to boiling in 3-quart saucepan; reduce heat.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir remaining ingredients.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2 inch wide sticks.
Place in old water (ice) about 30 minutes.
Pat dry.
Place potatoes in plastic bag with other ingredients.
Shake to coat.
Arrange on large cookie sheet in a single layer.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes, stirring once or twice until golden brown.

title: salmon cheese pate
directions: Combine ingredients; sprinkle with parsley sprigs and refrigerate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on a cookie sheet.
Layer the rest of the ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon-broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Add all other ingredients.
The mayonnaise and sugar should be mixed together before adding.

title: finger salad(vegetable pizza)
directions: *Broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, peppers, celery, Cheddar cheese (grated for the topping), olives (if desired) or any other vegetables desired.

title: cheri-nut gems
directions: Soften butter; blend with sugar and cocoa.
Mix well, then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix.
Add cereal and chopped nuts; stir into sugar mixture.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: cherry enchiladas
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, water and vanilla.
Warm tortillas. Place one teaspoon of filling on tortilla and roll up.
Place each rolled up tortilla on 9 x 13-inch baking pan, sprayed with Pam. Pour mixture of butter, sugar, water and vanilla on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry supreme cake
directions: For cake, mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in tube pan.

title: chocolate pecan toffee
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over lowest possible heat. Remove from heat and add sugar; stir until well blended.
Return to low heat and stir rapidly and thoroughly with a rubber scraper and continuously scrape the side and bottom of pot until the mixture reaches a full boil.
When the mixture reaches a full boil, add the corn syrup and water and mix well.
Cover the pan for a few minutes to allow steam to dissolve any sugar crystals which may have formed on the side of the pan.
Remove cover and, with a pastry brush dipped in just a little bit of water, wash down the sides of the pan to remove any crystals that may still be there.

title: great garlic biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown round steak, after flouring, in pan with oil and onions. Mix meat and all other ingredients together and cook for 1 hour. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except oats, cook on medium heat until boiling.
Let boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat and blend in oats. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: tuna sandwich melts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except buns.
Fill buns with 1/3 cup tuna mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: okra pickles
directions: Wash and pack okra down in hot, sterilized jars.
Put a garlic bud, some hot pepper pieces and some dill seed in each jar.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil; pour into jars and seal at once. Let ripen for several weeks before opening.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook together meat, chili powder, salt and onion.
Drain after browning, then cook 10 minutes.
Spoon into 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer Ranch Style beans, then tortillas (small pieces), then Ro-Tel and then cheeses (shredded).
Spread soup over top of casserole; cover.
Bake at 250° to 300° until bubbly.

title: oven-fried potato skins
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Using a fork, prick the potatoes. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Cut the potatoes lengthwise into quarters.
Scoop out the pulp with a small spoon, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
Spray a cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Place the potato shells on the sheet with the skin sides down.
Spray the potatoes with the nonstick spray.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp.
Sprinkle the Monterey Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese on the potatoes, then bake about 2 minutes more or until the cheeses are melted.
Sprinkle with the green onions and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; stir until well blended. Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with meat.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat margarine.
Add peanut butter and sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Then add dry ingredients.
Shape dough into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Crisscross with tines of fork.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In saucepan, heat beets and juice on low heat.
Add sugar, vinegar and pickling spice to taste.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Let cool.
Pour over eggs.
Cover and store in refrigerator for several days until eggs are pickled as desired.

title: andy's infamous butter cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine.
Pat into greased cookie sheet.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender at high speed.
Makes 1 quart.

title: santa fe trail corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix, just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake in well-greased 8-inch pan at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until center tests done.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Mix these 3 ingredients and put in a quart jar.
Leave Starter on the counter for 4 to 5 days.
Set in refrigerator for 3 days. Take out of refrigerator and feed with the same 3 ingredients as listed.
Let set out for 8 to 12 hours.
Throw away 1 cup and refrigerate again for 3 days.
Take out of refrigerator and feed again.
Leave out 8 to 12 hours.
Throw away 1 cup; refrigerate again for 3 days, then take out and feed again.
Leave out 8 to 12 hours.
This is the third feeding, so you're ready to take out a cup and make the bread.
Return the remaining to refrigerator and feed every 3 to 5 days with the 3 ingredients to keep the Sourdough Starter usable.
After each feeding, either throw away 1 cup or make bread to give to a neighbor.

title: quick chili
directions: Melt shortening in heavy skillet.
Add onion; cook until brown.
Add ground beef; brown.
Stir often so there will be no lumps of meat.
Add pepper, tomato soup, salt, chili powder, black and red pepper and kidney beans.
Heat mixture thoroughly; serve piping hot.
Serves 6.

title: butter crumb cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and sugar.
Combine butter with dry ingredients, crumbling with fingertips.
Take off 3/4 cup of mixture for crumbs for top, then add well beaten egg, milk and vanilla gradually.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into well-buttered loaf pan.
Add crumbs to top and sprinkle cinnamon over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new england crab spread
directions: Mix cream cheeses together.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch serving plate.
Combine remaining ingredients, except the crabmeat. Spread over cheese.
Spread crabmeat over sauce and garnish with parsley.
It should look like a pizza when finished.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving with crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O per box directions in a large bowl.
Place in refrigerator while preparing other ingredients.
In another large bowl, place cranberry sauce, cream cheese, celery, pineapple and nuts.
Mix and pour into the Jell-O.
It's more solid if made the night before or, after combining all ingredients, you can pour into a rectangular shallow pan and cut into small squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except grapes.
Add grapes.
Stir. Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour thoroughly with sugar, add slightly beaten eggs. Add butter and salt to sugar mixture.
Add syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pie crust and bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for 50 minutes.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan.
Heat on medium heat until hot. Delicious with grilled cheese sandwiches on cold winter evenings!

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Beat together milk and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and chill.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat; blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth; remove from heat.
Stir in milk and cheese.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until thickened.
Arrange alternate layers of ham, potatoes and broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and sugar together; add milk.
This will make a medium batter.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to 2 cups fresh peaches or a No. 2 can of peaches with tapioca.

Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine in a baking dish; add peaches and tapioca. Pour batter over top of peaches and bake in a 350° oven until batter is golden brown, approximately 15 to 30 minutes, depending on oven.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: skillet barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil.
Stir in barbecue sauce, water, corn and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Gradually stir in pineapple.
Grease the bottom of a tube pan.
Add batter; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until cake tests done.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
In large bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Combine all other ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Stir just to moisten.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into prepared pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pans 10 minutes and remove to rack to cool.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: In saucepan, add flour, mustard, sugar, salt and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add cream and beat, then add vinegar, a little at a time.
Cook over a pan of boiling water or stir constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens.
When cool, pour over cooked, diced potatoes, onions, celery seed and boiled eggs.
Mix thoroughly.

title: freezer strawberry preserves
directions: Clean and drain strawberries.
Add 2 cups sugar and cook at low heat until sugar dissolves, then boil for 3 minutes hard.
Stir often, then add 2 cups sugar and boil 2 minutes longer.
Cool and freeze.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: hominy casserole
directions: One can of Cheddar cheese soup can be substituted for the Cheez Whiz.

title: extra special baked chicken
directions: Run cold water over dried beef; drain.
Arrange in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place halved chicken breasts over beef.
Top each half with a slice of bacon.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In a large bowl, stir together sugar, nonfat milk powder and creamer powder.
Sift in cocoa.
Stir to thoroughly blend all ingredients.
Fill a 1-quart size jar with mixture.
Insert vanilla bean down center of jar to add flavor.
Screw on jar cap tightly.
Store in a cool, dry place.

title: johnsonville sausage and potato skillet
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Add sausage, onion, hash browns, bell pepper, black pepper and garlic.
Saute over medium heat for 9 to 11 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Transfer to a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or cast-iron skillet.
Spread condensed soup evenly over vegetable mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle parsley and fried onions on top.
Serves 8.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes. Let drain, then cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Combine soup and sour cream; mix in shredded carrots.
Add squash and onion to soup and cream mixture (do not mash).
Use about 3/4 pack of dressing.
Add melted margarine to stuffing and mix.
In casserole, put layer of stuffing, then spoon squash mixture on top.
Add another layer of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple kuchen
directions: In a medium-large bowl, cut margarine into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Spray nonstick spray on a 9 x 13-inch aluminum baking pan.
Pat dry cake mixture lightly into pan (don't press), building up edges slightly.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Arrange apples on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.
Mix sour cream and egg. Drizzle over all.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Serve warm or chilled. Refrigerate leftovers.
Also delicious using fresh peach slices.

title: easy cherry cake
directions: Put can of pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top of filling.
Lay slices of oleo over mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. (Blueberry or apple pie filling may be used.)

title: bibingka(baked mochi flour)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Combine fresh milk and coconut milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Fold in tsubushian.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into desired serving size.
Serve either hot or cold.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.

Thaw and drain the broccoli and place in the bottom of pie plate. Sprinkle with onion and cheese. Place milk, Bisquick mix, eggs, salt and pepper in a blender. Cover and whirl for 15 seconds or else beat with hand mixer.
Pour into pie plate. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Have butter standing in mixing bowl at room temperature. Beat sugar into butter with electric mixer.
Add egg and beat well.
Resift flour with baking powder.
Adding 1/4 at a time, blend flour into beaten mixture.
Line cookie sheets with foil. Use cookie press.
Decorate with red, green or other sprinkle sugars.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 - 10 minutes.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: 1000 calorie pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed, substituting Carnation cream instead of milk.
Add water, mixing until firm.
Add cream cheese and mix. Fold in Cool Whip and add pineapple.
Chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Fill greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
For corn muffins, bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill about 4 hours.

title: crispy vegetable salad
directions: Combine broccoli, carrots, red pepper, radishes and celery with salad dressing. Toss. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 15 minutes. Toss with salad mix before serving.

title: melon chicken salad
directions: Pare cantaloupe and cut into four crosswise slices.
Remove seeds and cut out inside of cantaloupe rings to leave a one-half inch ring.
Reserve cut-out melon.
In large bowl combine reserved melon and cut rest of melon into cubes.
Cut into cubes chicken, celery, radishes.
Mix with blue cheese dressing, cover and chill several hours.
To serve, place melon slices on salad plates and spoon chicken salad in middle of each ring.
Garnish with celery leaves.
Serves 4.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, then add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Glaze with mixture of approximately 1/8 cup lemon juice
and 1 cup confectioners sugar.

title: muffalatta
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate 12 hours.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Put hamburger in a kettle with a little water.
Cook until almost done, then add onion, ketchup, vinegar and mustard and cook until well done.
Mash the hamburger well.
Cook on low heat.

title: rotel dip
directions: Drain vegetables; melt cheese.
Use hand mixer to blend.
Good with taco chips.

title: spinach stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut off top fourth of each tomato.
Reserve for other uses. With a small spoon, scoop out pulp to make hollow shells.
Chop pulp; let drain in a colander.

title: go to bed mints
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat well egg whites and cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar, salt and coloring.
When all is stiff, stir in chocolate chips (or use regular chocolate chips and add mint flavoring).
Drop on cookie sheet.
Turn off oven.
Put cookies in.
Take out in morning.

title: beefy enchilada skillet
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet until brown and drain fat. Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares. Add sauce, tortillas and 1/2 of cheese to meat. Let come to a boil. Cover and cook on low heat for 5 minutes or until hot. Top with remaining cheese and sour cream.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: perfect meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Don't overbeat the egg whites before adding the sugar or the meringue will leak, making the top of the pie filling moist and slipping.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff glossy peaks form and sugar dissolves.
Rub some meringue between your fingers.
You should not feel any sugar granules.
Spread meringue over hot filling.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Fold in prepared Dream Whip.
Spread this on chilled crumb mixture.
Chill several hours more.
Before serving, add pie filling.

title: hermits
directions: Mix well.
Spread onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°. When cool, cut.
Frost with:

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Mix in peanut butter, blending with a fork.
Stir in milk and egg.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with Raisin Butter if desired.
Makes 15 servings.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, eggs and vegetable oil (batter will be thick).
Add mandarin oranges (including juice); fold together. Pour batter into well-greased 8 x 10 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown. Let cool completely.

title: annie's german plum cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together, then add eggs until smooth.
Stir in sifted flour and baking powder and add vanilla. The batter will be thick.
Spread into a baking pan (9 x 13-inch), ungreased.
Cut plums in half, removing pits and rinse.
When dry, place plums, skin side down, on top of batter until it is covered. (I find it usually takes about 21 plums to cover the whole pan, 42 halves, 6 across and seven down).
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 to 3/4 hour until batter is browning on the edges.
If the plums are properly ripened, they will create a syrupy glaze over the cake.
This cake is like nothing else I've ever tasted.

title: santa fe pot roast
directions: Combine chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Make small slits in roast; in each slit, insert some of the spice.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine egg white in cold water.
Beat until frothy (not stiff).
Add pecan halves.
Mix until coated.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add nuts; mix thoroughly.
Place on buttered 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 225° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken in mushroom sauce
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery and Lipton onion soup mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Add 1 can Campbell's mushroom soup.
Smother for 1 hour.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir at least 1/2 of mixture into egg yolk.
Blend into remaining mixture.
Boil 1 minute more. Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Add coconut to taste.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Spread between layers and frost with 7 Minute Frosting.

title: cherry delight
directions: Pour all ingredients together and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: trash vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill; best 12 hours before serving.

title: raspberry-nut cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt or tube cake pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Fold in vanilla and spices.
Pour chopped nuts in bottom of cake pan.
Carefully pour batter over nuts.
Bake in a preheated oven per package instructions.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: summer bombe
directions: Select a bowl and measure it in cups, allowing at least 1 cup per person.
Line bowl with ladyfingers.
Pack bowl with lemon ice cream (other flavors will do but lemon is best).
Freeze.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Measure liquid and add water to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin mix.
Stir in fruit.
Pour into 2-quart flat casserole and place in refrigerator until firm.
Combine next 4 ingredients and blend well but do not beat.
Spread over congealed salad and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Serves 12.
This can be used for a salad or dessert.

title: pecan butterball cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar; stir in vanilla.
Work in flour; add nuts.
Take a pinch of dough and form in a ball size of a large marble.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: newman road kill stew(great way to clean out your freezer)
directions: Use your favorite to your taste:
salt, savory salt, black and/or red pepper, garlic or onion salt plus herb or two with light hand:
summer savory, oregano, basil or whatever you like.
Throw kill, onion and seasonings into a large pot.
Cover with water. Cook, partially covered, over medium heat until meat is tender (time depends on "kill").
Remove all bones and return meat to pot. Add tomatoes including juice and stir-fry veggies.
Simmer until veggies are tender.
Serve hot to brave friends or cowardly enemies.
Will serve hundreds if it's been a long time since you cleaned out your freezer.

title: hershey marshmallow dessert
directions: Prepare a graham cracker crust in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt marshmallows and milk over low heat.
Stir until completely melted (I use my microwave).
Remove from heat.
Let stand and cool. Fold whipped cream into marshmallow mixture.
Add grated Hershey bar.
Save enough chocolate to sprinkle on top of dessert. Refrigerate and serve.

title: holiday pumpkin pie
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and ginger.
Cut in the shortening.
Add the walnuts and mix.
Stir in water.
Shape into a ball.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with the pastry.
Trim and flute the edges.
Chill for 15 minutes.

title: egg roll filling
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet.
In a large bowl combine all vegetables and meat.
Blend in Accent, blend in egg and soy sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Put 2 Tbsp. of mixture on egg roll wrapper and roll up, brush ends of egg roll wrapper with water and corn starch mixture to seal well.
Deep fry until nice and brown.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix and lay on lettuce.
May sprinkle with coconut.

title: western bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet or saucepan.
Transfer to baking pan and add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Dice bacon; fry crisp.
Drain on paper towel and cool.
In bowl, mix together bacon, onion and mayonnaise.
Remove stems from tomatoes.
Place stem side down on a cutting board.
Cut tomatoes, making an X so you can scoop out pulp.
Invert and drain.
Fill with bacon mixture.
Chill for several hours.

title: chocolate scotheroos
directions: In a 3 qt. sauce pan combine sugar and corn syrup, cook over medium heat stirring constantly until bubbles.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until completely melted.
Add rice Krispies.
Spread in buttered 13x9-inch pan.
Melt both kinds of chips and spread over mixture in pan.
Let harden several hours and cut into squares.

title: peppery herb rib steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, except steaks.
Arrange steaks in shallow baking dish and cover with peppery herb mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain and save liquid.

title: candied pecan sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into casserole.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg and next 4 ingredients (parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce).
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown meat balls.
Remove meat balls from skillet.
Pour off fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in skillet, stirring constantly until jelly is melted.
Add meat balls and stir well and until completely coated. Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: party punch for kids
directions: Partially defrost lemonade and strawberries.
Pour chilled ginger ale over.
Make frozen mold with Hawaiian Punch.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft, not mushy.
Peel and cut in half lengthwise.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add sugar.
Add water and bring to boil, then add sweet potatoes.
Cook slowly until liquid is thick and the potatoes are brown.
Serves 6.

title: tea cakes
directions: Put eggs in medium sized bowl; beat them well.
Add sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.
Now add flour and mix well to make a soft dough.
Drop from tablespoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: christmas toffee bars
directions: Mix and pour in pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cool and cut in small squares.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let items sit at room temperature before mixing.
Roll into size balls you want.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: date salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and whipped cream.
Add dates, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Mix together and put in refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.

title: crispy lemon-fried chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a large bowl; add 3 teaspoons salt, lemon juice and enough water to cover chicken.
Soak in refrigerator overnight.
Drain thoroughly.
In a paper bag combine flour, paprika, pepper and remaining salt.
Toss chicken pieces in flour mixture; shake off excess.
Heat about 1/2 inch of oil in large skillet.
When hot, carefully add chicken and brown lightly on all sides, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables, salt, pepper and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir well.
Add mixture to frozen pie shell.
Top with remaining pie shell.
Punch holes with fork in top pie shell.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.
Or, follow directions on package of frozen pie shells.

title: chocolate candy drops
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
After melted, stir in nuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper and let harden.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Add milk, butter, salt, remaining sugar, eggs and 3 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes, adding additional flour as needed.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch down; shape into rolls of desired size.
Place in greased pans and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rabbit
directions: Boil rabbit until tender in water with salt and onion.
Put in baking container and bake until brown.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in greased baking dish.
Mix milk with mushroom soup and pour over beans. Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shannon's dream bars
directions: Prepare pan with margarine and 1/4 cup flour.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine on low in saucepan.
Add the 1/2 cup brown sugar and the 1 cup flour.
Stir until mixed.
Dump mixture into a 9 x 6-inch pan.
Press the mixture evenly over the bottom and sides of the pan like a crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: trapper's sweet bannock
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and water and mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Spread in well greased skillet.
Cover and cook slowly on back of grill over hot coals.
Or bake in preheated oven at 350 for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tropical carrots
directions: Cook carrots about 15 minutes.	Drain.	Combine other ingredients and cook until thickened.
Heat carrots with thickened mixture.

title: tapioca
directions: Combine milk, tapioca, egg yolk and salt.
Mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until boiling.
Stir once during preparation.
Let cool, covered, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: snickers ice cream
directions: Finish filling ice cream freezer with milk and freeze.

title: baked chicken with vegetables
directions: On square of foil, place chicken breast rib side up.
Fill hollow where ribs are with potatoes, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Put tablespoon margarine on top.
Close foil wrap.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cheese, eggs, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Place about 1 tablespoon of cheese mixture in the center of each chicken breast.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
In a large skillet, thoroughly brown chicken on all sides in hot oil; drain off fat.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bulgogi-marinated beef
directions: In a blender, blend garlic, onions and soy sauce.
Add the next 4 ingredients and blend.
Remove from blender and add sesame seed, green onions (to taste) and vinegar.
Pour sauce over meat and mix well.
Let the meat soak overnight in a covered bowl in the refrigerator.
Cook the next day in the crock-pot 1 hour on high and 2 to 3 hours on low.
Serve over rice.

title: grandma's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until mixture is desired consistency.

title: pie blitz
directions: Put pie mix in dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of this. Sprinkle on pecans, then pour melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheese candy
directions: Melt cream cheese in a double boiler.
Mix in sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Drop immediately by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: tomatoes blue
directions: Place tomato slices on a baking sheet.
In a small bowl, combine butter, Blue cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley with a fork until well blended.
Add enough crumbs to make a crumbly dough.
Divide evenly among tomato slices and press to form a "crust" on each.
Broil until topping is brown and bubbly and tomatoes are heated through.
Serves 6.

title: chicken biscuit bake
directions: In a bowl, combine the soup, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in chicken, broccoli and onion.
Transfer to a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Separate biscuits; cut each in half. Arrange, cut side down over hot chicken mixture.
In a bowl combine remaining ingredients and pour over biscuits.
Bake uncovered, 20 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Yield:
6 - 8 servings.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs in a bowl. Add 2 Tbsp. parsley, bread crumbs, broth, garlic, salt, tarragon, mustard and pepper.
Beat well.
Mix in ground beef.
Set aside.

title: old fashion cookies
directions: Cream vegetable oil, oleo and both sugars.
Add flour and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir and blend.
Roll balls, marble size, into granulated sugar and press with glass.
Bake about 12 minutes at 375°.

title: hershey's chocolate mint bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 10 x 15-inch pan. In large mixing bowl, beat flour, sugar, eggs and syrup until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes (until top springs back when lightly touched) or cake starts to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in order.
Bake until bubbly at 350° or microwave on High until bubbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together hamburger, 1/4 c ketchup, salt, pepper water, onion soup mix, bread crumbs, and egg.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Makes about 30 punch cups.

title: batter yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, egg, and 1 cup flour.
Beat well until smooth.
Add remaining flour, a little at a time, and beat well.
Grease muffin pan.
Fill each muffin half full.
Let rise in warm place, free from drafts for about 30 - 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 18 - 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco until light. Add eggs. Beat well.
Add orange juice, pumpkin and milk.

title: grandmom's potato rolls
directions: Heat milk until scalding; remove from heat.
Add potatoes and margarine to melt.
Add sugar and salt.
Sprinkle yeast over mixture while warm.
Let set 10 minutes.
Add sifted 6 to 7 cups flour.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Let rise in greased bowl until double.
Punch dough down.
Pat into walnut size pieces to form cloverleaf rolls in muffin cups.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.
Let rise again until double.
When risen, bake until brown.
Put small pat of butter on top of each roll.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, sour milk, soda, baking powder, nutmeg, salt and flour.
Roll and cut.
Bake 10 minutes at 450 degrees (I bake mine at 300 degrees as my oven is very hot). Add currants or coconut to batter if desired.
I make mine plain.

title: butter horns and triangles
directions: Mix flour and butter; work in cottage cheese.
Chill at least 8 hours.
(Dough can be kept chilled for several days.)
Divide dough into 4 portions.
Roll one portion at a time on very well-floured board.

title: swizzle steak
directions: Brown meat in frying pan. Add onion. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes*, adding additional water, if necessary.
Before serving, add 1 tablespoon cornstarch to a small amount of water and mix into meat to thicken sauce.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old sugar cured kentucky ham
directions: *I just get a cured ham from the grocery; it never weighs 20 pounds and I don't know how old it is.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Mix onion, garlic, parsley, bell pepper, mushrooms and oregano.
Add rice; pour into a baking pan.
Put sliced eggplant on top of rice mixture.
Pour tomato sauce and Mozzarella cheese on top of eggplant.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when done.

title: chocolate tornado
directions: Spoon whipped topping evenly into 6 dessert dishes.
Using back of spoon, spread whipped topping into the bottom and up sides of each dish.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Spoon pudding into dishes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana "n" walnut lite delight
directions: Toss bananas with lemon juice.
Layer fresh fruit, yogurt, bananas and nuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into lightly greased casserole dish (approximately 8 x 8 1/2-inch size).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Dip should be brown on sides and bottom, makes 2 cups.
Serve warm.
Good with wheat crackers or vegetables.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and pour directly into ice cream freezer. May be made in homemade freezer.

title: beer-based glaze for ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ham fat side up in roasting pan. Pour all but 2 tablespoons of the beer on top of ham. Bake until cooked through, about 1 hour, basting occasionally with pan juices.

title: sausage snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Roll into small balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chili rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Season rice with salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, salt and chiles.
Place a layer of rice, cover with a layer of the sour cream mixture and top with strips of cheese.
Repeat, making 2 or 3 layers and ending with rice on top.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Lightly
grease
x
13-inch	pan.
Separate crescent dough into
2 large rectangles.
Press rectangles over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of pan to form crust; seal perforations. Bake crust
at 375° for 5 minutes.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over partially baked crust.
Bake at
for 18 to 22 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ethel's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix alternately with milk and eggs.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 1 teaspoon almond flavor.
Add 1 cup nuts.
Bake in well-greased tube pan for 1 hour or until done.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put Oreos in blender to crush and set aside.
Cream together the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar and set aside.
Blend pudding and milk and let it begin to set, then fold in Cool Whip. Blend in sugar and cream cheese mixture.

title: pot of chili
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Brown meat in olive oil.
Add garlic, onion and peppers; saute.
Add reserved juice and remaining ingredients except pineapple.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add pineapple and heat thoroughly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water just until tender.
Drain.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix; pat into bottom of casserole, reserving 1 1/2 cups for topping.

title: inmate roast beef spread
directions: Mix everything except the flour tortillas together and heat thoroughly. Place mixture in flour tortillas and enjoy. Serves 4.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt butter in pan and pour into a baking dish.
Follow with graham cracker crumbs and spread evenly.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Follow with coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pat ingredients down to make even.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until coconut is browned.
Let cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: turkey or chicken salad with boiled dressing
directions: Mix everything together and cook until thick, stirring most of the time.
Then cool and add as much mayonnaise as necessary and pour over chicken or turkey salad.
Make to taste.
If dressing is sour, add more sugar or more water (or milk).

title: chili con carne(easy but tasty)
directions: Sear ground beef at high temperature in a large pot.
Reduce temperature, pour off grease and add corn oil.
Add onions.
Cook with beef at lower temperature until translucent.
Add green peppers.
Cook until texture is to your taste.
Add canned tomatoes and can of beans.
Add from second can of beans to your own desired amount.
Rinse tomato and bean cans with one or two ounces of water; add to pot.
Add teaspoon of bouillon powder; stir well. Add chili powder to taste.
Add one or two shakes of garlic powder or one or two cloves of fresh garlic cloves.
Stir well and simmer 15 or 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Melt margarine, oil, water and cocoa in saucepan.
In mixing bowl, put sugar and flour.
Add melted ingredients, then add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.

title: parmesan taters
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash potatoes, leaving peeling on.
Cut in quarters.
Roll in cheese, flour, salt and pepper mixture. Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Melt butter and add to potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake 20 minutes or more until tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: kraut relish
directions: Put in large jar with lid; press down so sauerkraut is covered with the liquid.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours.
Good on burgers.

title: m&m's party cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add
dry
ingredients
to
the
sugar
egg mixture. Blend well.
Stir
in
cup
of
M&M's (save remaining for decoration).
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook or heat the beets.
Boil together the remaining ingredients until thick and clear.
Add some butter or margarine about the size of a walnut.
Add the beets and mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of large Pyrex dish.
Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Make layers with potatoes and other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours covered with foil.

title: tater tots baked dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Place Tater Tots in bottom of casserole.
Pour hamburger mix on top of Tater Tots. Pour creamed corn on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato with jacket on until well done.
Peel and mash while hot (do not add anything extra to potato).
Add margarine and gradually add sugar until all mixed.
Roll out mixture very thin (1/8 inch) and spread peanut butter over all.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Slice in 1/4 inch slices.

title: tang dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust. Spread Cool Whip on top of filling.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread	apple
pie
filling
in
long
buttered pan and sprinkle
with cinnamon.
Cook white sugar, flour, salt, water and butter.
Pour over apples and top with flour, rolled oats, salt, brown
sugar
and Crisco.
Mix together and sprinkle on top.
Bake in moderate oven 35 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Put oats in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes. Remove. Stir in nuts, coconut, wheat germ and powdered milk.
In separate bowl, combine honey, oil and vanilla. Stir everything together.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir everything 3 to 5 minutes. Cook until golden.

title: scalloped peppers
directions: Go to deli, buy potato salad.
Put in pretty bowl.
Slice hard-boiled eggs over top and garnish with parsley.

title: marinated carrots(a great cookout dish and easy to make!)
directions: Layer drained artichoke hearts in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer drained spinach next.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and margarine until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk. Spread over top of spinach.
Sprinkle with pepper and grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package.
To rice, add butter, corn, onions and soup.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and add grated cheese to top.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: mexican puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine buttermilk, baking mix and water to make a dough.
Add sausage, cheese and pepper to dough.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Cook together until thick eggs, sugar, butter and vinegar. Add 2 cups pineapple, 2 oranges, 2 cups white grapes or cherries and 1 cup marshmallows.
Fold in 1 cup whipped cream and let stand 24 hours.

title: banana mallow pie
directions: Toast coconut with margarine

in a skillet on low heat until golden brown. Pat into pie plate to form crust. Cool in refrigerator. Mix pudding mix with milk. Add marshmallows and 1/2 Cool Whip. Slice bananas in cooled coconut shell. Cover with pudding, then top with Cool Whip.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt in double boiler the caramels and 1/3 cup of milk until very thin.
Keep hot.
Mix cake mix and butter and then mix in 1/3 cup milk.
Take half and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and refrigerate.

title: batter for onion rings
directions: Beat egg yolk.
Add oleo, salt, 1/4 cup milk and flour.
Add the other 1/4 cup milk.
Beat egg white and fold into batter.

title: company chicken
directions: Roll chicken and wrap 1/2 slice bacon around and anchor with toothpick.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon cream of celery and chicken soup and sour cream over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marmalade drop cookies
directions: Beat sugar and butter until light and creamy.
Beat in egg and marmalade.
Mix flour and baking powder, add to butter and egg mixture.
If mixture is too dry, add a little more marmalade.
Drop the batter from a teaspoon about 2-inches apart on a greased sheet. Bake the cookies in 375° oven for about 8 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut fruit and nuts in large pieces.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Scatter half cup of dry ingredients over fruit and nuts.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually, creaming until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
To creamed mixture add fruit and nuts and remaining dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Makes 150. Will keep well for several weeks or may be frozen.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil peppers for 5 minutes, and cool.
Mix raw rice and uncooked ground chuck with chopped onion and add 1/4 to 1/2 cup catsup, stuff into pepper shells and put into baking dish.
Cover with mixture of the tomato soup, water and the remaining catsup. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put all the ingredients in bowl.
Add one 8 ounce bottle Kraft coleslaw dressing. Mix.
Ready to eat.
(Can add crisp fried bacon, crumbled.)

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve as a dip for raw vegetables. Can be used with fruits, grapes and apple slices.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: Combine apple cider, cranberry juice, brown sugar, lemon peel, cinnamon sticks and cloves in saucepan.
Mix well.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Pour into cups.
Makes 12 servings.

title: salmon dip
directions: Puree salmon.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook spaghetti according to box directions.
Drain.
Put spaghetti into a large bowl.
Add butter and eggs.
Mix well.
The hot spaghetti will cook the eggs.
Add bacon, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: corn supreme
directions: Heat the corn and milk, then stir in the egg.
Now, add the rest of the ingredients except for the buttered crumbs.
Mix well.
Pour in a dish; add buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: some of terri's soup(cemetery soup)
directions: Brown hamburger or ground turkey.
Drain.
Add the onion.
Add everything else.
Add the water.
Cook on low fire.
Cook for 3 hours.

title: deer roast
directions: Place the deer in a roast pan with an onion (sliced or whole). Salt and pepper.
Fill the pan with water to cover meat.
Cook for 3 hours at 350°.
Place the potatoes and carrots around the roast and cook 1 hour longer.
Drain the broth off the roast into a saucepan.
Mix about 3/4 cup flour with hot water in a jar.
Shake well until lumps are gone.
Pour the flour mixture into the broth, stirring constantly.
Now, heat the broth up, stirring constantly, until desired thickness.
You may need more flour, depending how thick you like your gravy.
Just remember the secret to no lump gravy is shaking the flour and hot water in a jar, then stirring into broth; last, heating and constantly stirring until thick.

title: cheryl ladd's raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: lemon fluff(low calorie)
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Put jello, milk and sweetener in blender.
Blend 30 seconds. Refrigerate until partially set. Blend again for 30 to 45 seconds.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch dish or 4 small bowls.
Refrigerate.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into a 1-quart casserole dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Line bottom with bread slices.
Put sausage over bread.
Mix eggs, milk, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until eggs are done.

title: saucy kielbasa appetizer
directions: Boil kielbasa for 5 minutes.
In a plastic bowl, place water, butter and entire box of brown sugar.
Microwave for 2 minutes or until mixture is melted.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of mustard until smooth.
Taste and add more mustard if desired.
Slice kielbasa into bite size pieces.
In a large dish, combine sauce and kielbasa and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: inspiration soup
directions: Simmer 20 minutes (unlimited).
(Weight Watchers Inspiration.)

title: big bag wolf's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with shortening.
Melt the butter and chocolate in a large saucepan over low heat.
Remove the saucepan from the heat.
Stir in the sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Add eggs and beat well with a beater.

title: kids' delight cookie bars
directions: Place butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until melted.
Tilt pan to coat evenly with butter.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle Kavli crumbs over butter.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs. Top evenly with remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack in pan.
When completely cool, cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.
tags: thick style Kavli Norwegian crisp bread crumbs

title: scrumpous pie
directions: Mix and pat evenly in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown at 350 degrees. Cool completely.

title: strawberry cheesecake trifle
directions: Cut up strawberries and mix with glaze.
Then take the angel food cake and break up and put in a punch bowl.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix in large bowl. Roll into balls. Place meatballs in a large pot of boiling water. Cook until meatballs float to the top.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix flour, brown sugar, sugar, cinnamon, salt and oil.
Remove 1/2 cup of flour mixture to use as topping and mix with pecans and set aside.

title: chocolate goodies
directions: Heat milk and chocolate chips together.
After mixture is hot and melted, add remaining ingredients.
Drop onto wax paper and let set up in refrigerator.

title: salami potato swirl
directions: Pare the potatoes.
Cut into quarters.
Cover with water.
Add onion and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until just tender, not mushy.
Drain (save potato water for soup).
Mash potatoes.
Add butter, milk, eggs and black pepper.
Whip until fluffy.
Stir in salami, cheese and green onions.
Spoon into a buttered ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Heat under a broiler until crusty or at 450° for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and make into meatballs.
Brown in oven until done.

title: no fuss lasagne
directions: Cook noodles separately.
Follow package directions.
Cook hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients to hamburger.
Cook slowly until blended well.
Alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheese in baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted through and through at 350°.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Layer bananas and vanilla wafers in a large casserole dish. Combine pudding, Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and milk.
Blend with mixer for 5 minutes, then pour mixture over bananas and wafers; chill.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together in microwave for 2 minutes on High power.
Stir all ingredients together with wire whip.
Put in about a 9 x 13-inch casserole microwave dish.
Cook on 50% power for 9 minutes; rotate at 4 minutes.
Then cook on High power for 5 minutes.
Put marshmallows over top and melt on top the last few seconds of cooking.

title: nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add water and beat again.
Add sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Beat again.
Add crackers and walnuts.
Stir. Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour mixture in plate. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. When cool, refrigerate. Add whipped cream before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup, water, garlic powder and mushrooms.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Take off heat immediately and add sour cream.
Cook wide noodles and pour sauce over them.

title: hummus ii
directions: Drain and wash the chick peas.
Boil in little water till the chick pease are very soft.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in dish (9 x 13-inch).
Add all ingredients; mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese into the bottom of glass dish. Then spread chili over cream cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the chili. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese starts to bubble. Serve with either Doritos or Tostitos.

title: fresh fruit pies
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crusts. Chill for 1 hour.
Yields 2 pies.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, dump undrained crushed pineapple and cherry pie filling into pan.
Swirl around until well mixed and corners filled.
Sprinkle the yellow cake mix over the top. Drizzle the melted butter and then sprinkle the nuts on.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: creamy ambrosia
directions: Fold whipped cream and sour cream together. Drain fruits. Stir fruit, coconut and marshmallows into cream mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: judge ray lee jenkins' special brown sugar pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Beat this mixture at least 15 minutes.
The trick is in the beating.
Grease loaf pan heavily as much as you can.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: deluxe pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1 cup water for 10 minutes.
Bring pineapple juice and fruit, lemon juice and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add gelatine.
Let mixture cool until partly set, then add grated cheese and whipped cream.
Place in 12 to 14 individual molds and chill until firm.
Serve with following dressing.

title: chili
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onions and green pepper in large pan until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: ring of fire chili
directions: Brown ground chuck in large skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Saute onions and garlic in oil in skillet for 10 minutes. Add oregano, chili powder, cumin, red pepper, tomato paste, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in bouillon cubes dissolved in water and beer.
Add ground chuck; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans.
Simmer for 30 minutes longer.
May chill overnight and reheat for best flavor.
Serve with plenty of bread and beer.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix well.
Divide.
Color and flavor.
Roll into small balls. Dip in granulated sugar.
Press flat or in mold.
Let dry overnight.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in bowl and mix thoroughly with mixer.
Pour into can; add condensed milk and stir well.
Add dairy milk to fill and stir.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Cook meat, onions, pepper and tomatoes together until rice cooks.
Layer sauce, then rice and beans; finish with meat sauce. Add cheese topping.

title: macaroon kiss cookies
directions: Beat butter, cream cheese and sugar in large bowl until well blended.
Add egg yolk, almond extract and orange juice; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture.
Stir in 3 c. coconut.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.
Shape dough into balls; roll in coconut and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately press Hershey Kiss on top of each cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and onion.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain sauerkraut and spread over cream mixture.
Break up 1 can corned beef and spread over kraut.
Add Swiss cheese, grated on top.
Remove crusts from rye bread.
Tear bread in pieces and put on top of cheese.
Drizzle margarine slowly over all.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes; while still hot, add the butter, cinnamon, sugar, raisins, and pecans. Pour into greased
or sprayed baking dish. Cover with marshmallows. Bake in 350° oven until heated through and the marshmallows are browned.

title: french dressing chicken
directions: To make sauce, combine all ingredients except chicken and rice.
Put chicken into greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1-1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk and flour, beating well.
Cook two layers plain.

title: apple salad
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Mix in pineapple with juice.
Cook until thick (4 to 5 minutes).
Add margarine or butter; let cool completely.
Chop apples, one at a time; add to mixture.
Add a little Cool Whip to mixture.
Put in dish.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip; top with nuts and cherries.
You can put half of the nuts in mixture and the other half on top.
Cool 24 hours.

title: sweet cheese mold
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in raisins, pecans and chocolate chips.
Shape in ball and chill. Serve with graham crackers, cookies, celery, etc.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix throughly.
Roll into balls or put green olives, cashews, or small weiners in center of cheese balls.
These will keep for a long time in the refrigerator or they can be frozen.
When ready, Bake at 400° for 10-12 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash the potatoes.
Add sugar, eggs, spices, salt and milk. After mixed, place in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Place steamer rack over 1 inch boiling water in saucepan.
Add green beans.
Cover and cook for 4 minutes.
Add mushrooms. Transfer to serving bowl.
Combine water and mustard in small bowl; pour over vegetables.
Add butter; toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease loaf pan with butter.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Beat in eggs and oil and dry ingredients.
Don't overmix.
Gently stir in berries.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, according to oven.
Lightly browned and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool before inverting pan.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk. Bring to a
boil on medium heat and continue to boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove
from
heat	and
quickly
add
vanilla, salt (optional), peanut
butter
and
oatmeal.
Mix	well.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed
paper
and cool.
Next, watch them disappear.

title: texas salad
directions: Toss together the lettuce, beans, Cheddar cheese, tomatoes, onion and Catalina dressing.
Just before serving, crush Fritos and toss again.
Use about 1/2 bag Fritos.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: braised turkey patties
directions: Form 6 patties with the first 3 ingredients; brown in a little oil or Pam.
Remove from pan.
Make gravy in same pan according to directions on envelope.
Put patties back in pan; add sliced onion over all.
Cover; simmer slowly until onion is cooked.
If too thick, add water.
Recipe is fat-free.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake as directed on box.
Let cool; split layers in half with a string.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour over top of batter in cake pan. Sprinkle with pecans or coconut if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place 3 slices of onion on bottom of each jar and add 1/2 teaspoon dill seed and cucumbers sliced lengthwise.
Add 1/2 teaspoon alum to each jar.
Mix together vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and pour over pickles in jars.
Add 2 slices of onions and 1/2 teaspoon of dill weed on top of each jar and seal.
This recipe is for quart jars.

title: cinnamon swirl pudd'n cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, water, margarine and vanilla extract in bowl.
Blend well and then beat at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top of batter.
With knife, cut through to spread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "hot" barbecue chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in half.
Dust in mixture of flour and chili powder. Fry in hot oil 8 to 10 minutes on each side until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Heat together barbecue sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Add chicken wings and simmer a few minutes.
Makes 24 "hot" wings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into large Pyrex (9 x 13-inches).

title: buttered chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Cream with butter. Add flour and eggs. Add vanilla, salt and nuts. Bake in well-greased 8-inch cake pan at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Add seasoned salt and bread crumbs.
Mix in meat and enough water to thin a little.
Bake at 300° until done, about 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. (4 slices bread, diced and 4 tablespoons butter.
Melt butter and toss in crumbs.)

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together and pour half of mixture in bottom of pan. Cover with uncooked rice and chicken. Cover with remaining soup mixture and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Blend in soup and milk; add tuna.
Meanwhile, cook noodles and drain.
In casserole combine noodles and tuna mixture.
Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients together and form into balls.
Dip in sugar.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nana's party mix
directions: Melt butter and mix together with Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Mix together, in large roasting pan, the butter mixture with cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Bake in 250° oven for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes to coat all pieces well.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Soak marshmallows in milk in refrigerator overnight.
Cut candy in small pieces and combine all ingredients.
Press in square pan.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Chop celery and onions to the size that please you.
Chop both kinds of olives.
I buy large pitted black olives.
Chop ham, cheese and pepperoni to a size that pleases you.
I buy a pound of cheese and a
pound of baked ham unsliced.
I also buy the sliced pepperoni and just cut it in half.
Cook your shells per package directions and drain.
Add it all together in a bowl and add dressing.
I usually make it a day in advance so that it's cold and the dressing and flavors mingle.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/4 cups.
Saute onion in shortening in large skillet until tender.
Add 1 1/4 cups water, carrots and bouillon or broth. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and ginger. Add catsup, vinegar and soy sauce and stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook until clear and thick.
Add chicken, green pepper and pineapple.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: vendors waffles(preparation time:  5 minutes.  cooking time:  6 minutes)
directions: Mix eggs with milk and salt.
Sift flour and baking powder together, then add to liquid.
When ingredients are mixed, stir in lard.
Bake in waffle iron until done.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix soup, broth, Ro-Tel and onion.
Pour over chicken breasts and Doritos.
Layer Velveeta cheese over that and cook until cheese melts.
Cook on about 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend sugar and flour.
Continue blending egg, pineapple juice and margarine.
Heat on medium, stirring constantly, until thickens (takes about 15 minutes).
Cool.
Fold in 1 pint whipping cream.
Cool and serve.

title: rocky road candy crisps
directions: Put butter, 3 cups marshmallows, chocolate chips and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Put in greased casserole.
Put buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook slowly for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Pour into clean, hot jars and seal.

title: pretzel surprise
directions: Mix crushed pretzels sugar and oleo.
Press mixture in Pyrex dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat 1 cup sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour over cooled pretzel layer.
Mix boiling water with Jell-O.
Add strawberries.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 12 or more.
Chill one hour.
Store in refrigerator.

title: steamed vegetables
directions: Place carrots and potatoes in a steamer; cover and cook for 6 minutes.
Add sprouts.
Cover and cook for 5 to 7 more minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Combine margarine, lemon juice and pepper; toss with steamed vegetables.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Saute onion in margarine, add soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling, add potatoes.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes until heated through. You can vary this dish by adding either diced ham, smoked sausage or pepperoni.

title: lime cream fruit mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add lime juice. Beat in sour cream with wire whip.
Add pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cherries and pecans.
Turn into mold and chill until firm.

title: ice box cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix with mixer butter and both sugars. Add eggs, creaming mixture.
Mix dry ingredients and add gradually. After well mixed, stir in vanilla and nuts with spoon.
Roll into logs then roll logs in floured cling wrap.
Store overnight.
Slice and bake.
Dough lasts for a long time in frig.

title: cheese and bacon muffins
directions: Mix together.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12.

title: delphine's famous oatmeal chocolate chips cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes in very lightly greased pan.
Do not overbake.

title: summer garden pasta
directions: Combine tomatoes, green onions, parsley, basil, wine vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Heat olive oil in a medium skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Saute garlic in hot olive oil until golden brown.
Remove skillet from heat and discard garlic.
Pour the garlic oil over the tomato mixture and toss gently to coat.
Cover tomato mixture with plastic wrap. Chill for at least 3 hours.
Cook pasta using package directions; drain well.
Place in a warm serving bowl.
Add chilled tomato mixture to pasta and mix well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Serve with crusty French bread if desired.

title: beef topped pasta
directions: Prepare vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain. Meanwhile, in 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, broccoli and pepper. Heat through, stirring as needed.
