Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until center is set.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix caramel sauce and milk, leaving about 2 tablespoons of caramel in jar.
When cake is removed from oven, use a meat fork to put holes all over top of cake.
Pour caramel and milk mixture over cake.
Let soak in and cool completely. Spread Cool Whip over cooled cake and top with crushed Heath bars. Drizzle remaining caramel sauce over Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: chili balls
directions: Mix beef, pork, egg, rice, milk, 1 teaspoon chili powder and salt.
Form into small balls.
Brown in hot fryer.
Combine tomatoes, water, onion, salt and remaining chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Drop balls into mixture.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: You also need 100% cotton kitchen string.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Partly peel cucumbers, leaving strips of green and slice thin. Add salt to cucumbers and let stand for 15 minutes.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Press excess liquid from cucumbers and add to sauce.
Chill and serve as relish.
You may add small pieces of thinly sliced mushrooms, carrots or abalone to decorate this relish.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out bottom crust to fit into a 9 in. pan.
Break Ritz crackers coarsely into sauce pan.
Combine water, sugar, and cream of tartar.
Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice.
Cool. Pour into pie shell. dot with butter.
Add top crust and crimp edges.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Make two or three slits to let steam escape.
Bake in preheated oven at 370 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix
all
ingredients thoroughly and chill before serving. Makes 60 cups.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add milk, corn and salt.
Melt butter in baking dish; add corn mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, peanut butter and melted butter together to make a thick batter.
Take and roll the mixture into small balls and then freeze until very hard.

title: scalloped green beans
directions: Place beans in bottom of buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix soup, onion, bacon, cheese and Tabasco.
Pour soup mixture over beans.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until nicely browned and cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: andrea's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add oatmeal, flour, salt and baking soda.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yogurt topped apples
directions: To make filling:
In small mixing bowl, combine raisins and nutmeg; set aside.

title: muffins by the pailful
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store, covered, in refrigerator.
Bake next day or after, at 375° for 15 minutes in muffin cups, 2/3 full.

title: pistachio nut torte
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add flour and chopped nuts.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 6 ounces Cool Whip and spread on top of crust.
Combine pudding and milk, beat on low for 2 minutes.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer. Top with 10 to 16 ounces Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Add chopped nuts.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Set aside.
In 15 x
10-inch baking dish, put uncooked rice.
Layer pork chops with green pepper slices, tomato slices and onion slices.
Salt and pepper well.
Pour consomme over all; rinse the cans with a little water and add to casserole.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven until liquid is absorbed and vegetables are done,
approximately 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: crock pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and set aside.
In a saucepan, mix vinegar, water, salt and sugar; boil 1 or 2 minutes.
Place cucumbers in a crock, layering cucumbers, then onion, fresh dill and garlic cloves; repeat.
If large cucumbers are used, cut in 2 or 3 pieces. Pour vinegar mixture over top and weight down cucumbers by placing a plate and a weigh on top.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours, then remove weight.
Cover and refrigerate.
These pickles will keep for months.
Yields 2 gallon jars.

title: tuna and biscuit roll
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Cook onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour, add milk and cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Stir in tuna. Prepare biscuit mix according to directions.
Roll dough into rectangle about 12 inches long and 1/8 inch thick.
Spread with tuna mixture.
Roll like a jelly roll and seal ends and edge.
Vent top of roll.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Be creative and shape roll like fish.)

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sugar and salt together in shallow dish. Heat shortening in skillet or on griddle.
Dip bread slices, one at a time, into egg mixture.
Turn and coat evenly.
Fry until lightly brown on both sides.
Serve with syrup, jelly or 10xxx sugar.

title: oreo cookie supreme
directions: Layer bottom of pan with cookie crumbs.
Pour over Eagle Brand milk; layer again.
Pour over prepared pudding.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Cover with Cool Whip before serving.

title: grandma's carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil & sugar, cream well. Sift in dry ingredients. Fold in carrots and nuts. Bake 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean, at 350°. Makes 3 layers or 1 9 x 13 cake. Top with cinnamon cream cheese frosting.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the eggs, zucchini, oil, pineapple and vanilla.
Combine the dry ingredients; stir into egg mixture just until moistened.
Fold in nuts and raisins if desired.
Pour into two greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add salt, sugar and oil, blending well.
Stir in 2 cups of flour and beat well; add remaining flour slowly to form a soft dough.
Knead well.
Store in a greased bowl with cover overnight in refrigerator.
Punch down dough; make into rolls.
Leave rolls on baking pan until they rise double in size, 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: chili dip
directions: In crock-pot, mix all ingredients together.
Stir occasionally.
Great with Doritos or any kind of chip.

title: zesty scalloped potatoes
directions: In saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add potatoes, onion, garlic, bouillon and salt.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring.
Cover and lower heat.
Cook about 10 minutes, until potatoes are almost tender.
Spread 1/2 potato mixture with liquid in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Cover evenly with 1/2 cheese and 1/2 chilies.
Repeat with remaining potato mixture, cheese and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: southwest stew
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Add onions. Pour into pot. Add all other ingredients. Bring to a boil and turn down heat. Let simmer for about 20 minutes. Serve hot, topped with grated cheese and tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: no baked cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients.
Drop from spoon onto wax paper.

title: fiesta potato dippers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Toss potato wedges with oil and chili powder.
Transfer to cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix together cheese, sour cream and cilantro until well blended. Makes 1 cup.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
While noodles are cooking, heat butter over water, both in chafing dish, until melted.
Stir in cream, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese and salt.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Drain noodles; toss with cream mixture until evenly coated.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bass's squash delight
directions: Place about 3/4-inch of water in saucepan.
While bringing water to boil, add sugar, salt and pepper.
Have burner on high at all times.
Cook fast to a boil that can not be stirred out.
Add pre-cut squash and other ingredients (except margarine) finely chopped.
Cover until tender.
Continue to boil hard until all the fluid is gone.
Stir regularly.
Add margarine.
Stir until melted. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand until served.

title: chocolate covered peanut balls
directions: Melt margarine; stir in peanut butter and powdered sugar and mix well.
Add graham crackers, coconut and chopped nuts.
Roll into small balls.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients together in a bottle and its ready to use.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: Using a whisk or hand mixer, whip milk and peanut butter.
Add pudding and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Gradually add half and half. Stir until thickened; add Parmesan.
Cook and stir until smooth. Fold in crab delights; heat 3 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Toss fettucini with sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Bake in 13 x 9 pan.
Cool. Punch holes in top with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour cream of coconut over top, then pour on Eagle brand milk.
Layer cool whip and top with frozen coconut.

title: molasses fruit cake
directions: Put all together and knead to a stiff dough.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Use dried fruit to stack.
Sweeten the dried fruit and add spice and a little cinnamon.

title: coach thompson's sugar cookies
directions: Mix well.
Pinch small balls; put on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. While hot, dip in confectioners sugar.
Nuts and chocolate chips may be added to dough.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let rise once.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Melt butter.
Cut biscuits out and drop in butter.
Keep layering in Bundt pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: dilly beans
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in bottom of each pint jar.
Put the beans in four pint jars.
Bring the water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour brine over beans.
Seal with Ball type lids.
Makes 4 pints.
Does not have to be processed.

title: chocolate chip cookie sensation
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Stir pudding and half and half together and put in refrigerator for 15 minutes. Flatten cookie dough with fingers in a sprayed pizza pan. Soften cookie dough first. Bake 10 to 12 minutes and let cool completely.

title: cranberry almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg and beat well. Blend in almond extract. Combine flour, salt, cranberries and almonds.

title: lasagne(serve with french bread)
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce, parsley flakes, sugar, salt and basil.
Heat to boiling; simmer 45 minutes uncovered.
Save 1/2 the sauce for top.
Mix cottage cheese with the remaining 1/2.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
No grease in dish.
Alternate noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese mix 3 times.
Top with 1/2 meat sauce and 1/4 Parmesan cheese.
Let sit 15 minutes before cooking.

title: easy toffee(servings:  4)
directions: Line jelly roll pan with saltines.
Bring brown sugar and butter to a boil.
Pour over saltines.
Bake in 375° to 400° oven for 7 to 9 minutes.
Sprinkle chips over hot candy.
Spread when melted.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Break like peanut brittle.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, cream and flour.
Cover and chill. Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/3 of dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on floured cloth-covered board.
(Keep remaining dough chilled.)
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Transfer rounds with spatula to piece of waxed paper that is heavily covered with granulated sugar; turn each round so that both sides are coated with sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick rounds with fork about four times.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or just until set, but not brown.
Cool.
Put cookies together in pairs with Creamy Filling.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: party punch
directions: The night before, slice oranges and place in a bowl with water; freeze.
When ready to serve, place 7-Up in punch bowl and scoop out sherbet into punch bowl.
Place ice with oranges in bowl and serve.

title: marinated tomato and cucumber salad
directions: Combine tomato wedges and cucumber and onion slices in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine vinegar, oil, mayonnaise, sugar and salt.
Beat using a wire whisk until smooth.
Pour dressing over tomato mixture, tossing gently.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with slotted spoon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Line bottom and sides of 9 x 12-inch pan with graham crackers. Mix together pudding and milk, mix until smooth, add Cool Whip, mix until smooth.
Pour into pan, put graham crackers on top of pudding mixture.
Melt frosting in microwave for 1 minute.
Pour over graham crackers.
Refrigerate until frosting hardens.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients thoroughly, then add the pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: betty maloney's fruit salad
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and lemon juice until thick.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: orange-pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix milk and pineapple in churn container.
Add Sunkist drink to fill line of churn.
Churn.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Sift the flour and salt together; cut Crisco into flour mixture with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Mix egg, vinegar and cold water together.
Add to flour mixture and work with hands to form
smooth
ball.
Roll
out into circles and put in pie pans. Fill with favorite pie filling and bake.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain and mash into fine pulp.
Add beaten eggs, onion, grated cheese and white sauce.
Cook in a double boiler 1 hour.
Place in a 2-quart casserole together with bread crumbs and bake at 375° until crumbs brown.
(Can cook in double boiler the day ahead, then bake later.)
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs with hand beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust. Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes longer or until knife stuck in center comes out clean.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop oranges (with peel), pecans and cranberries.
Put in bowl.
Sprinkle sugar over top and let set for 10 minutes, then stir.
Put 2 cups boiling water and Jell-O into mix.
Mix together well.
Pour into a long dish and chill overnight.

title: iced tea
directions: Boil 4 cups of water.
Tie tea bags together; add to water as it starts to boil.
Turn fire off.
Let tea seep for 15 minutes (no more than 30 minutes).
Add sugar to dissolve.
Pour tea water into gallon container.
Run cold water over tea bags; add to enough cold water to make 1 gallon of tea.
Do not squeeze tea bags.
Makes tea bitter.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir and pour into crock-pot, chafing dish or fondue pot.
Serve with crackers.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, celery, pepper, pimentos and onion together.
Mix well the sugar, oil and vinegar.
Add to kraut mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread dough on pizza pan.
Spread sausage on dough, then cheese, then hash browns.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat
eggs;
add sugar, oil and zucchini, beating after each addition.
Sift
dry
ingredients
and
add
to zucchini mixture. Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for 2 loaves,
30 minutes for 12 "Texas" muffins and 20 minutes for 24 regular muffins.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in Eagle Brand milk, ReaLime and food coloring.
Turn into shell.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, not dry. Spread on top and seal.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green chiles casserole
directions: Break eggs into a large bowl, and beat until light.
Add remaining ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Pour into a well-greased 2 quart baking dish, and bake in a 350 degree oven for 1 hour, or until top of casserole is browned and center is firm.
Cool for 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Warning:
Do not allow any water or steam near chocolate, or it will hunk up.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Hard-cook eggs; boil for 10 minutes and peel eggs.
Pour beet juice into measuring cup.
Place beets and eggs into container. Measure equal amounts of vinegar and sugar to beet juice.
Combine beet juice, vinegar and sugar in saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Pour liquids over the beets and eggs.
Let stand at room temperature for several hours, then store in refrigerator for several days.
To serve, place on egg tray or other serving dish.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Resift flour with baking soda and salt.
Cream the butter until soft.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat well.
Mix flavoring with sour milk.
Stir dry ingredients alternately with sour milk into creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients and mixing until smooth after each addition.
Stir in rhubarb and nuts.
Pour batter into two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Combine 1 tablespoon melted butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: cheese - vegetable soup
directions: In a 4 quart saucepan, combine potatoes, onions, carrots, celery, water, margarine and bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. In small bowl, combine milk and flour, beat until smooth. Gradually blend into vegetable mixture.
Add cheese, mustard and pepper.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.

title: pizza dough
directions: Add
yeast
to warm water and let dissolve.
Add sugar, salt, oil and 1 cup of flour.
Mix.
Gradually add the remaining flour until dough forms a ball.
Knead with dough hook or by hand until dough is no longer sticky.
Spread on pizza pan. Add
sauce,
your favorite toppings and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl. In a separate bowl, mix the molasses, oil, egg and hot water. Beat dry ingredients into wet ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef; rinse and drain.
Add minced onion and bell pepper.
Add spaghetti seasoning, tomato sauce and 1 cup water. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
When ready to use, mix 3 or 4 large bottles of 7-Up with frozen mixture.
This serves around 50 people.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let dough stand at room temperature until soft, not puffy. Roll out to size of cookie sheet.
In a small bowl, mix eggs, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread 3/4 of mixture on dough.
Place sliced pepperoni and cheese on top.
Roll up dough into long shapes. Seas ends well.
Cut in half and seal those ends also. Bake in two loaf pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Before baking, spread rest of egg mixture on top.

title: apples and peanut butter wedges
directions: Cut the apple into wedges and apply peanut butter.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Cream the cream cheese, then add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into cupcake liners in muffin tins.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°. Remove from oven; cool 5 minutes.
Cakes will fall slightly, leaving a small depression in the center.
Fill each depression with 2 teaspoons of Sour Cream Mix. Drop small dab of your favorite jelly or jam on top of each cake.
Return to 300° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
Refrigerate.
(These may be frozen for up to a month.)

title: deviled crabs
directions: Cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, cooking until thick, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Stir small amount of hot sauce into egg, blending well; then add to sauce. Add parsley and crabmeat.
Place in well-greased shells.
Combine crumbs and 1 tablespoon butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place flaked tuna, cheese and sliced eggs in a casserole dish. Pour soup and milk over mixture.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and crumbs brown.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Combine corn, green pepper, pimento, celery, onion and oil; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently, cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: cocktail franks
directions: Saute onion and celery in hot oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Simmer about 45 minutes. Can make ahead and freeze.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat together.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add all together with milk and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.
Don't open door.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers. Soak overnight in salted water (1 handful of salt for every 1/2 gallon of water).
Drain.
Cover cucumbers with boiling water.
Allow to stand for 10 minutes.
Drain and pack into sterilized jars.
Combine vinegar, 1 cup water and sugar. Bring to a boil and allow to boil for about 10 minutes.
Pour hot vinegar solution over cucumbers in jars.
Seal.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together; bake in buttered dish at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush garlic in small bowl; cover with oil.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Fry bread cubes in 1/4 cup garlic oil.
Cook eggs 1 minute in boiling water.
Remove and cool.
In small bowl, combine lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and anchovies.
Mix well.
In large bowl, tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Drain oil from garlic; toss into salad.
Add mixture; toss.
Add bread and cheese.
Toss well and serve at once.

title: sensational stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems.
Chop enough stems to make 1/2 cup. Cook mushroom caps in margarine 5 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and Parmesan cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add chopped stems and onion; mix well.
Fill mushroom caps.
Broil until golden brown.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: better than ? cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake in 11 x 16-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix pineapple with sugar. Boil 5 minutes.
When cake is done, punch holes in top and pour pineapple over the cake.
Let cake cool.
Mix pudding as directed.
Pour over cake. Sprinkle with coconut.
Slice bananas over cake and cover with Cool Whip. Cover with nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Stir butter into potatoes. Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk; add honey. Mix baking powder, sugar and flour. Add milk and potatoes. Press into a circle 3/4-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 17 to 18 minutes. Yield: 16 to 18 biscuits.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream, milk, salt, pepper, 1/2 cup melted butter and cream of chicken soup.
Mix in Cheddar cheese and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush corn flakes and mix with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Put on top of potato mix (don't blend in). Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: famous pumpkin pie(makes one 9-inch deep dish pie)
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt for 10 minutes.
Add butter and boil to soft ball.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.

title: squash stuffed chicken
directions: In a skillet, melt butter or margarine over medium heat. Saute onion, parsley and basil until the onion is tender.
Add zucchini and continue to cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat; stir in bread crumbs, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper. Carefully loosen the skin on the chicken on one side to form a pocket.
Stuff with zucchini mixture.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is done.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave pecan pie
directions: Put butter in medium mixing bowl, microwave on High until butter melts.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes until smooth.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust.
Microwave on High for 15 to 17 minutes or until set.
Rotate pie plate every 5 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: mashed potato and cheddar casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 2-quart souffle or casserole dish. Cook potatoes until tender. Drain and mash.
Add butter and eggs. Beat until smooth and airy.
Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to baking dish and sprinkle cheese over.
Bake until cheese is melted and potatoes are heated through (about 20 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: grandma's graham cracker cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Crush graham crackers and mix in baking powder.
Add cracker mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Blend in pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake 1 hour.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 8-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream oleo, sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Add sour cream and nuts.
Pour into greased pan; sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until nice and brown.

title: stephanie mclaughlin's fudge drops
directions: Combine butter, milk and sugar in pan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Stir vigorously 1 minute. Working quickly, drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: cheese roll
directions: Blend cheeses and garlic. Add chopped nuts.
Make balls or roll. Cover with chili powder or additional chopped nuts.

title: finger lickin' barbecue
directions: Marinate meat according to package directions.
When coals are white, place meat on the grill.
When meat is nearly done, baste with sauce.
Place in pan and cover with heavy foil.
Place pan on an area on the grill where the heat is not direct for 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine onions, cucumbers and salt.
Cover with ice and let set 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add crushed garlic and whole mushrooms.
Gently mix in lemon juice and shrimp.
(Add more butter, if needed, at this time.)
Saute 1 minute on each side, or until pink.
Add wine; increase heat and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add cornstarch mixture.
Return to flame until sauce is thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Blend in sugar, shortening and salt.
Beat egg with fork; add to mixture.
Add 1/2 the flour; beat 150 strokes with wooden spoon.
Add remaining flour; beat 150 strokes or until blended.
Grease large bowl.
Put dough in bowl; lightly grease with some of the butter.
Cover, let rise in warm place until doubled (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch dough down and turn in bowl.
Lightly grease top with butter. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
(May be kept several days in fridge.
Keep top greased and bowl tightly covered.
Use as needed.)

title: spicy crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in egg; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in greased shallow baking dish. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Combine all ingredients in a big skillet.
Cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.

title: corn custard mexicana
directions: Thaw corn.
Place in large bowl.
Add melted butter, beaten eggs, corn meal, salt, pimiento, celery, sour cream and cheese. Rinse seeds from chilies; chop.
Add to corn mixture and mix well. Pour into buttered casserole (1 1/2 quarts) and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set and golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
5 or 10 minutes until it is done cover with velveeta cheese.
Finish baking.

title: chili parlor chili
directions: Bring 1 quart of water to a boil.
Add ground beef; crumble and cook until meat is no longer pink.
Add the rest of the ingredients; spices first.
Let simmer for 6 to 8 hours.

title: crunchy romaine toss
directions: Brown chopped walnuts and broken noodles in butter.
Break lettuce into salad bowl.
Add coarsely chopped broccoli, chopped onions and remaining ingredients.
Toss with Sweet/Sour Dressing.

title: sunshine spinach salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing mix with vinegar, orange juice and water as directed on envelope,
substituting orange juice for the 2 tablespoons water and adding orange peel.
Mix spinach, orange sections, onion and turkey bacon in large bowl.
Add dressing; toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cool cherry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand together.
Refrigerate for an hour.
Add the cherries, coconut, nuts and marshmallows. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yield:

title: parmesan chicken(microwave)
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Place margarine in small bowl. Microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Mix together Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, parsley flakes and garlic powder.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Roll in melted margarine and then in bread crumb mixture.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish with meaty ends of chicken on outer edges of the dish.
Sprinkle with paprika on top of chicken pieces.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave for 12 to 14 minutes on High, turning chicken halfway through baking time.

title: buckaroons
directions: Cream together	shortening
and
sugars.
Add
eggs and beat until fluffy.
Mix	flour,	soda,
salt and baking powder together and add
to
sugar mixture.
Mix in oatmeal, vanilla, chocolate chips and
nuts.
Drop
on	greased cookie sheet and bake for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: quick 'n easy scotchie buns
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Dip each biscuit in melted margarine until thoroughly coated, then roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
In a well buttered salad mold or Bundt pan, place biscuits in pan to form a ring.
Sprinkle approximately 1/3 of butterscotch pudding mix over top of biscuits.
(Save the remainder for 2 more batches.) Sprinkle with chopped nuts and bake at 350° until brown.
Serve hot.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish and put a layer of onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Bring rice and chicken broth to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
Drain.
Add pecans, raisins, orange peel and onions.
Mix oil and orange juice; pour over salad. Refrigerate.
Serve at room temperature.

title: orange muffins with topping
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, blend together the orange juice concentrate, orange marmalade, buttermilk, vegetable oil and egg substitute. Add to the flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spray muffin cups with nonstick vegetable cooking spray; fill 2/3 full in a small bowl.

title: chocolate cake roll
directions: Beat 4 egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Beat 4 egg whites; add vanilla and sugar.
Fold in egg yolk mixture.
Add flour and cocoa.
Put in buttered wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When baked, put on powdered sugar towel and roll like a jelly roll.
Put in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, spread with ice cream and roll back up.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate-filled angel torte
directions: Combine pudding mix with the milk. Heat to boiling, stirring, and cook until the mixture boils and is thickened.
Cool slightly. Stir in the sour cream and rum.

Split angel food cake into 3 layers. Spread chocolate mixture between the layers, stacking layers back on top of each other again. Whip the cream and add the powdered sugar to sweeten slightly. Spread over top and sides of the cake.
Decorate top with chocolate curls or shaved chocolate. Serve immediately or cover with a dome and refrigerate up to 3 hours before serving.

title: corn relish
directions: You will also need six pint jars with lids.

title: black forest punch bowl cake
directions: Put a layer of cake in punch bowl.
Top with pudding.
Spread cherry pie filling over pudding.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Repeat until punch bowl is full.
Top with Hershey bar and cherries.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Add tomato soup and green beans.
Mix and put into baking dish.
Mix instant potatoes by package directions.
Add beaten egg to potatoes and spread over beef mixture.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy minestrone soup
directions: In saucepan, brown bacon and cook onion, celery with garlic and basil until tender.
Stir in soups, water, tomatoes, macaroni and salt.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and zucchini, cooking 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.

title: anise cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs and sugar; combine.
Mix dry ingredients, then add to egg mixture.
Add milk and anise.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix.
Roll in 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar. Tip:
Roll balls with wet hands to keep from sticking to hands.

title: grandma's gingerbread cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 325° to 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
It will be better if it is prepared and refrigerated overnight.
Garnish with paprika.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Sprinkle generosity with kindness; add plenty of faith. Spread over a period of lifetime and serve everybody you meet.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Drain peaches and mix with butter.
Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl to make batter and pour over peaches. Sprinkle mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon on top of batter. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mama's sunday tea
directions: Using the 6 tea bags, prepare tea the way you normally would, using 2 1/2 quarts of water and adding the cloves or mint leaves. Remove tea bags and cloves or mint immediately.
Sweeten to taste while tea is still hot.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice; chill.
After desired temperature, add soda or ginger ale just before serving and stir lightly.
Serve with lemon garnish in tall, chilled glasses.

title: christmas bread
directions: Saute pepper and onions in melted margarine.
Cut biscuits in four (4) pieces each.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan, ungreased.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Then cut up into small pieces. Place half of the chicken in the bottom of casserole dish.
Then pour cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Then
place remaining chicken in dish and cover with cream of chicken soup.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top and drizzle with butter.

title: one day sweet pickles
directions: Mix well with hands the pickles, onions and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain well and squeeze out juice with hands.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth.
Makes 2 full glasses.

title: bread and celery stuffing
directions: Pour water over bread and let stand for 20 minutes.
Squeeze out extra water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Make just before serving cooked turkey or roasted chicken.

title: cole slaw
directions: *Fat-free ingredients may be substituted.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Saute the onion until limp and mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes and put into casserole.
Cover and reheat leftovers.

title: ham ball
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl except crackers.
Mix well. Shape into a ball and place in the middle of a serving platter. Must be refrigerated overnight.
Arrange Wheatsworth crackers around ham ball before serving. Other crackers are fine, but these taste especially good with the Ham Ball.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Drain pineapple and mix together.
Add marshmallows and nuts and leave in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, add Cool Whip.

title: french doughnuts
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Add milk. When lukewarm, add the dissolved yeast.
Add beaten eggs and enough flour to make mixture thick.
Keep in refrigerator overnight or until cold.
Roll out in flour.
Cut into doughnuts. Fry in 400° to 425° shortening.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Heat griddle slowly while mixing batter.
Beat egg well.
Beat in buttermilk, shortening, flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Pour onto hot, lightly greased griddle.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together and chill.

title: no cholesterol apple cake
directions: Cream together the sugars, oil and egg whites.
Add to the mixture, in order, the flour, whole wheat flour, oat bran, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice (or nutmeg) and the apples, mixing well after each.
Spray Pam on 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tina's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix with other ingredients and form a ball.
Can be rolled in nuts.

title: barbecue deer
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot until tender.
Remove from pot and tear apart.
Remove broth from pot.
Replace meat.
Add sauce, carrot and onion.
Season to taste.
If too thick, add some broth.
Simmer 2 hours on low.
Serve on a bun.
Can add all the broth and leave juice to serve over noodle.

title: mexican dip
directions: Gather 10 or 12 friends of the bride to be.
Add a dash of lively conversation.
Drop in one very surprised guest.
Mix with appropriate gifts.
Top with food and refreshments.
Serve a decorated shower cake.
Take about two and one-half hours.
Makes one successful shower party.
